# Tests & coverage (`api/`)

## When tests are required (blocking)

If the PR modifies **business logic** in `api/src/**/*.service.ts` or adds new service methods:

- Expect a corresponding `*.spec.ts` in the same feature folder.
- Flag if service logic changed but no test file was added or updated.

## Test structure

- Co-located `*.spec.ts` next to the file under test.
- Mock at boundaries: `PrismaService`, HTTP clients — not private methods.
- Use `@nestjs/testing` `Test.createTestingModule`.

## What to verify in tests

| Layer | Focus |
|-------|-------|
| Service | Business logic, permissions, edge cases |
| Controller | Route wiring, guards, status codes (mock service) |
| DTO | Invalid input rejection (when project tests DTOs) |

## Coverage gaps to flag

- Happy path only — no error/permission-denied cases for auth-sensitive code.
- Deleted or weakened assertions to make tests pass.
- Tests that mock everything and assert nothing meaningful.
- E2E tests that require live PostgreSQL without documenting skip/CI strategy.

## Commands

PRs touching `api/` should pass:

- `cd api && npm run lint`
- `cd api && npm run build`
- `cd api && npm run test` when logic changed

Flag PR descriptions that omit test evidence for non-trivial service changes.
